Xinhua Times: Turning Outstanding Returning Migrant Workers Into a New Force for Rural Revitalization - Xinhuanet
Talent is the key to the revitalization of villages.
Where is the talent to find?
Outstanding groups of migrant workers returning to their hometowns are an indispensable fresh force.
Xinhua News Agency Fat Shang Hai Chunzuo
Chengdu, July 26,2020/PRNewswire/-- Turning outstanding returning migrant workers into a new force for rural revitalization
Zhang Xiong, 34, whose family lives in Guoyuan Village, Meishan City, Sichuan Province, quit his job in Beijing in 2010, earning tens of thousands of dollars a month, and returned home to start his own business.
After several years of hard work, he now runs a family farm of grape growers with an annual income of more than one million yuan, and has become a leader in getting rich with a small reputation. He has also been selected to join the "two committees" team in the village.
In recent years, more and more outstanding migrant workers like Zhang Xiong have chosen to return to their hometowns to start their own businesses, activating a pool of spring water in the countryside, inspired by a series of policies to support farmers and benefit farmers, such as the national poverty alleviation and rural revitalization.
Sichuan, a province with a large population in the west of China and a large export of labor services, has implemented the "Excellent Migrant Workers Retroduction Training Project" because of snobbery. In 2019 alone, more than 8,000 village Party branch secretaries were created from the outstanding migrant workers, 61,000 village reserve forces were cultivated, and more than 20,000 Party members were developed, providing a strong guarantee for winning the war against poverty and implementing the strategy of rural revitalization.
Well-off is not well-off, the key is to look at the villagers.
Since the reform and opening up, a large number of young and middle-aged laborers in China's rural areas have gone out to work to increase their income, and some have set up their own enterprises through hard work.
But objectively, it also leads to the "hollowing out" of rural areas to varying degrees, especially the weakening of rural grass-roots organizations. Village Party branch secretaries and Party members present the characteristics of "one old and one low," that is, aging, low education, and the leading ranks of village Party organizations are not strong, and the problems of youth and youth are not prominent.
If the rural talents and other elements have been flowing to the cities in one direction, and the villages have been in the state of "blood loss" and "anemia" for a long time, revitalization is an empty word.
To attract back migrant workers who are capable, aware and interested in serving their hometowns, to guide them to return to their hometowns and start their own businesses to become leaders in getting rich, to train Party members and rural cadres on merit, and to enrich the ranks of cadres at the grass-roots level. This is the basic policy to solve the problem that the ranks of rural Party members and grass-roots Party organizations are not connected with each other.
Excellent migrant workers can be brought back, but also let them stay and do well.
In recent years, Sichuan has started by paying close attention to the Party building of migrant workers. On the basis of strict selection criteria, Sichuan has established such institutional mechanisms as targeted referral, service guarantee, training and energy promotion, and selection and use of outstanding migrant workers, so that they can improve their abilities, secure their work and have hope in life, truly take root in the countryside, and have a sense of accomplishment in starting their own businesses.
This year marks the end of the decisive battle against poverty. Talent is a key factor in connecting poverty alleviation efforts with rural revitalization.
Party committees and governments at all levels should attach great importance to the group of outstanding migrant workers returning to their hometowns. Through comprehensive measures, they should be made into a working team and a fresh force that can be retained, can fight and cannot be taken away, so as to provide a strong organizational guarantee and talent support for rural poverty alleviation and development and rejuvenation.
