Xinhua News Agency, Guangzhou, July 26 (Reporter Mao Xin) learned from the Guangdong Coast Guard Bureau that recently, the bureau, together with the Guangzhou Customs and Public Security Department, cracked down on an extra-large oil smuggling ring, and preliminarily verified that the gang had smuggled about 120,000 tons of refined oil since 2019, with a case value of about 800 million yuan and tax evasion of about 240 million yuan.
The Guangdong Coast Guard Bureau and the anti-smuggling department of the Customs have gradually worked out the division of labor and organization structure of the gang.
