Upgraded Russian helicopter gunship Ka-52M leaves factory for the first time at the end of the year - Xinhuanet
Moscow, July 25,2020/PRNewswire/-- According to the Russian Defense Ministry's plan, the Ka-52M, an upgraded version of the Russian helicopter gunship (hereinafter referred to as the Wuzhi) Ka-52, will be retooled and released from the factory for the first time in December this year. The Ka-52M will greatly improve its performance in reconnaissance, communications and weapons.
According to a recent report by the Russian newspaper Izvestia, Wuzhi Ka-52M is named "Super Alligator," and its development contract was signed by the Russian military and military industrial units in April last year. At present, the first two upgraded versions of Wuzhi are undergoing renovation and retooling at the Far East Helicopter Factory of the Russian "Progressive" Aerospace Corporation, and its state-level testing and improvement finishing work will be completed by October 2022.
According to the Russian experts who understand the above upgrade work, the "predecessor" of "Super Alligator" - Wuzhi Ka-52 was officially installed in November 2011. The model has exposed some weaknesses in its use, and this upgrade is to "fill the short board."
The report said that compared with the Ka-52, the Ka-52M will partially adopt a new type of protective material that will not increase its weight, and its pilot cockpit will be reinforced and equipped with new equipment to resist missile attacks, thus increasing the probability of battlefield survival; it will be equipped with a more powerful generator to power more complex airborne electronic equipment; the photoelectric system will be upgraded to be able to detect and identify battlefield targets that are farther apart; the new light multi-purpose missile equipped with the main attack armored fighting vehicles and reinforced concrete fortifications will have a range of 20 kilometers, which is about 1 times higher than the range of similar missiles used by the Russian military in active service; and its defense weapons and communication equipment will be used to the maximum extent possible with Mi-28NM gunship helicopters that can attack air targets, thus making the related maintenance easier and more economical.
In addition, the Ka-52M will have more advanced electronic guidance systems, weapon sighting systems and navigation equipment.
Russian experts also said that it is noteworthy that the Ka-52M will be equipped with communication equipment to communicate with UAVs, so as to obtain real-time information transmitted by nearby UAVs in the air, such as displaying the images taken by UAVs on the cockpit screen of the helicopter.
According to the plan, the pilots of the Ka-52M can directly control the UAVs with which they cooperate, thus improving the pilots' grasp of the battlefield situation and guidance of the long-range missiles.
According to Russian media reports, Russian Deputy Defense Minister Mikhail Krivoruchko said in December last year that the Russian Defense Ministry plans to purchase more than 110 Wuzhi Ka-52M aircraft by 2027.
