"Plugging into the South of the River" Pursuing the Poetic "Yellow River Dream" - Zhongxin
(China's Poverty Reduction Story) "Plugging the South of the River" Pursuing the Poetic "Yellow River Dream"
China News Agency Yinchuan on July 26 (Yang Di) "Nine Complex Yellow River Miles of sand, waves and waves from the horizon."
The Yellow River, which has aroused the pride of countless literati, has given birth to the beautiful and rich plains of Ningxia. Now, Ningxia, which has the reputation of "plugging into the south of the river," is adhering to the concept of "ecological priority and green development," and pursuing the poetic "Yellow River Dream."
The "Blue Wave Dream" of River Clear Water
"The Yellow River under the whole world is rich in Ningxia," and the Yellow River flows 397 kilometers through Ningxia, which is the "mother river" of the nurturing party.
However, with the rapid advance of industrialization and urbanization, there is an imbalance between the development, utilization and management of rivers and lakes, and chaos such as excessive discharge of pollutants, construction of land around lakes and encroachment on waters has come to the fore, resulting in black and smelly water bodies, excessive water quality, dirty environment and ecological degradation.
Now, Ningxia is promoting the diversified restoration of water ecology, and striving to restore the Yellow River to its beautiful and clear waters.
Water treatment should be done from the source.
In Yinchuan, Ningxia, the local government adopted the method of "bid raising + pollution control + strict control," all sewage in industrial parks was treated centrally, all sewage treatment plants in cities and towns were discharged under the Grade A standard, and the black and smelly water bodies in urban built-up areas were basically eliminated. The third batch of China's black and smelly water model cities was successfully declared.
In addition, Ningxia fully implemented the river and lake length system in 2017, and has now achieved the full coverage of the five-level river and lake length responsibility system in rural areas, cities and counties, and river and lake length patrol has become the norm.
Gu Jincheng, 64, who lives in a village near the Yellow River, witnessed the changes in the river: "The water used to have a bad smell, and after the remediation, the bad smell was gone."
Gu Jincheng said that the ecological environment is better, and his life is more comfortable. Now he often goes to the Yellow River for a walk with his family to feel the clear water and blue sky.
The "Wetland Dream" of Sand Gull Xiang Ji
Birds, green trees, boardwalk, clear water... Fan Zhongyan's "Sand Gull Xiangji" has become a reality in the Yellow River Wetland Park in Yinchuan, Ningxia.
The Yellow River flows through Ningxia, forming a variety of wetlands such as river wetlands, lake wetlands and swamp wetlands along the way, which plays an important role in promoting the rational utilization of water resources and the balance of water ecology. At the same time, it has also become an important migratory route for birds in the world.
Since 2009, relevant departments in Ningxia have invested a total of 3.45 billion yuan in wetland protection projects. At present, Yinchuan wetland covers an area of 19,200 hectares, with a wetland protection rate of 78.5 percent. There are nearly 200 natural lakes and swamp wetlands, and there are five national wetland parks, one national urban wetland park, six autonomous region-level wetland parks, and eight municipal parks.
Lu Jinhu, deputy director of Yinchuan Wetland Conservation Center, told reporters that wetland conservation has increased biodiversity, which is particularly evident in birds. "The gull is an endangered bird, and there are only more than 20,000 in the world, of which Yinchuan Wetland is home to more than 2,000."
At the same time, Ningxia has demarcated a 500-meter red line for wetland protection areas on both sides of the Yinchuan section of the Yellow River in accordance with the law, stipulating that no unit or individual may carry out development, construction or business activities within the scope of protection, except for public welfare projects.
Zhao Shaoyong, deputy director of Yinchuan Water Conservancy Service Center, said that through the treatment of pollution sources, the comprehensive improvement of river and lake ecology and the construction of wetlands at the end, the water quality of the nine main yellow drainage ditches in Ningxia has now reached 100% Class IV standard. "Now the water is clear, the fish have swum and the flowers have blossomed."
The "Drinking Water Dream" of Prudential Huimin
Ningxia Yinchuan once had an "awkward" title: The only city along the Yellow River that "guarded the Yellow River without water to drink."
Since 2010, Yinchuan City has been facing persistent water shortage during the peak summer period. The "pain of water shortage" in the past ten years has become a painful summer experience for many high-rise residents. However, under the current situation where major water sources are at the limit of overexploitation and large areas of groundwater overexploitation funnel have been formed underground in urban areas, water shortage has become a difficult problem for Yinchuan City.
Thanks to the improvement of the water quality of the Yellow River, drinking purified water from the Yellow River has become a good solution to the problem of drinking water for local residents.
Ding Ming, deputy director of Yinchuan Water Bureau, said that in order to improve the water demand of urban and rural residents in Yinchuan, Ningxia started the water supply project on the western line of urban and rural areas in Yinchuan metropolitan area in due course, and replaced the original underground water source with high-quality Yellow River water.
"On December 29,2019, the water supply project was officially opened to the three districts of Yinchuan City. In 2020, the residents of Minning Town and Helan County also drank the water of the Yellow River."
Ding Ming said that the water conservancy department of Yinchuan will consider the transformation of regional rural drinking water and urban water supply integration as a whole. "In the next step, we will integrate all the rural decentralized water supply points into the western water supply project. It is expected that by the end of this year, the urban and rural integrated water supply in Yinchuan will be basically realized."
