Xinhua News Agency, Shenzhen, July 26 (Reporters Mao Siqian and Bai Yu) encouraged residents to do medical check-ups and detect problems early; banned the sale of alcoholic beverages to minors; established a health review system for online games; employers should be equipped with full-time and part-time health management personnel... Recently, the "Shenzhen Special Economic Zone Health Regulations (Draft)" was officially released, and Shenzhen residents will have their own "Health Law."
In order to encourage residents to do medical examinations diligently and detect problems at an early date, the above-mentioned draft for soliciting opinions suggests that health departments should draw up basic catalogues of health examination items according to different age, occupation and other factors.
The health examination expenses that fall within the scope of the basic list of health examination items shall be paid by the overall fund of social medical insurance according to the standard of once a year for each person.
The draft makes it clear that the employing unit should rationally allocate human resources, arrange employees' working hours, and implement a rotational leave system for employees with heavy mental and physical labor load, so as to avoid excessive loss of human function or physical and mental health injury to employees' health, and at the same time strictly implement the system of paid leave for employees.
In addition, the employing unit shall be equipped with full-time and part-time health management personnel, and shall organize regular health check-ups for employees.
In terms of minors' physical and mental health, the draft for soliciting opinions proposes to prohibit the sale of alcoholic beverages to minors, and at the same time impose restrictions on the places where alcoholic beverages can be sold. Those who violate the regulations will be ordered by the market supervision and administration department to make corrections, and a fine of 30,000 yuan will be imposed.
In addition to "abstinence from alcohol," minors should also "exercise more."
According to the request of the draft, the school should arrange more than one hour of students' sports activities every day.
For online games, the departments of public security, culture, radio, television, tourism and sports, network supervision and health should improve the health supervision system of the Internet service business premises, establish a health review system for online games, and create a good communication space and culture for promoting the healthy growth of adolescents.
In addition, the draft also proposed that influenza patients must wear masks in public places, and medical and health institutions should be fined 20,000 yuan for revealing patients' privacy without their consent.
It is worth noting that in addition to the physical and mental health of residents, the draft also requires that all departments in Shenzhen should evaluate the impact of public policy implementation on the health of the population before formulating planning and normative documents concerning urban space planning and construction, industrial park planning and construction, resource development and utilization, ecological and environmental protection, biomedical industry development, as well as approving major construction projects and implementing major public service projects.
If it has not been assessed or will have a serious adverse effect on the public health of the city or the health of the residents, it may not be formulated, promulgated or approved for implementation.
