APEC Trade Ministers Meeting Says It Will Accelerate Regional Economic Recovery - Xinhuanet
Kuala LUMPUR, July 25 (Xinhua News Agency) (Reporter Lin Hao) Trade ministers of Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC) members held a video conference on July 25, pledging to work to reduce the impact of the coronavirus pandemic on the regional economy and accelerate the realization of a resilient, sustainable and inclusive regional economic recovery.
The meeting was chaired by Malaysia, the host of this year's APEC Economic Leaders' Meeting.
