Report says shared accommodation market has picked up since March - CNN.com
(Reporter Yang Zhaokui) "China Shared Accommodation Development Report 2020" (hereinafter referred to as the "Report") recently released by the National Information Center's Sharing Economy Research Center shows that due to the impact of the epidemic, the transaction volume of China's shared accommodation market decreased by 72.1% year on year in the first five months of 2020.
However, the shared accommodation market began to pick up in March, with the market gradually recovering in terms of transaction volume, order volume and reception numbers.
According to the report, the volume of transactions in the shared accommodation market fell sharply. On the one hand, the demand for travel accommodation dropped sharply under the epidemic prevention and control, and the volume of orders decreased sharply. In the first five months, the total volume of orders fell by 65% year on year, and the number of visitors dropped by 63% year on year. On the other hand, the weak demand also led to a significant decline in the price of overnight stays. In the first five months, the average price of overnight stays fell by 16% year on year.
However, in March, April and May, the market turnover increased by 78%, 199% and 35%, respectively; the number of orders increased by 141%, 152% and 50%, respectively; and the number of visitors increased by 81%, 112% and 28%, respectively.
"The report" pointed out that the development of shared accommodation industry is promising for a long time, but there are still many uncertainties in the near future.
In this regard, Yu Fengxia, deputy director of the Sharing Economy Research Center of the State Information Center, told the reporter of Workers' Daily that the development of shared accommodation needs stronger policy support. On the one hand, it is necessary to do a good job in implementing the policies already promulgated in the previous period, further strengthen policy advocacy, and focus on creating a better business environment. On the other hand, it is necessary to further strengthen policy guidance and support from various aspects such as stimulating consumer demand, enriching the supply of tourism accommodation services, innovating service methods, and strengthening cooperation between the government and platform enterprises.
