Xiamen, July 26 (Yang Fushan Zhang Shushan Xu Jingyi) China's famous vascular surgery center, Shanghai Changhai Hospital of Naval Medical University, signed a contract with Zhongshan Hospital of Vascular Surgery affiliated to Xiamen University on the 25th to jointly set up a cooperation center to promote exchanges and cooperation between the two sides in the field of vascular surgery, especially in the field of acute and severe diseases of the aorta.
According to Zhongshan Hospital affiliated to Xiamen University, after the two hospitals have officially formed a cooperative unit for vascular surgery, they will conduct remote consultation, formulate treatment plan with Changhai Hospital for real-time online consultation, select talents for further study and training, and jointly carry out weekly surgical technology exchange, teaching and checking rooms, etc. For complex cases, Changhai experts can be invited to perform surgery according to the needs of the patients, thus realizing that the patients in southwest Fujian can enjoy the top medical resources in the country without going to the province.
The two hospitals will also work together to carry out innovative research on surgery, popularization of aortic diseases and early screening, among others.
Organized by Beijing Health Promotion Association and hosted by Zhongshan Hospital Affiliated to Xiamen University, the special seminar on aorta was held in Xiamen on the same day.
The above-mentioned two well-known hospitals in Shanghai and Shanghai held the signing ceremony of the Vascular Surgery Collaboration Center at the same time, announcing the formation of a cooperative unit to jointly improve the level of treatment of vascular surgery-related diseases in southwest Fujian.
Shanghai Changhai Hospital Vascular Surgery is the only research institute of vascular surgery in the army and the only clinical medical center of vascular system diseases in Shanghai. It is also the first national key discipline of vascular surgery, leading the establishment of the professional committee of endovascular medicine of the Chinese Association of Physicians, and is a top team with deep accumulation in the industry.
Professor Huang Xiaojin, Director of Vascular Surgery of Zhongshan Hospital Affiliated to Xiamen University, was interviewed by the media.
Vascular Surgery of Zhongshan Hospital Affiliated to Xiamen University is the first vascular surgery in Fujian Province with an independent discipline. It has long been dedicated to the diagnosis and treatment of aortic and peripheral vascular diseases. In 2018, it was approved to build a provincial key clinical specialty.
In the treatment of aortic diseases, in addition to the treatment of dissecting aneurysms and aortic aneurysms, he has rich experience in the emergency treatment of ruptured aortic aneurysms.
"The history of vascular surgery at Zhongshan Hospital affiliated to Xiamen University, the breadth, difficulty and complexity of the operation, are outstanding in the region. Therefore, this time, we have set up a collaboration center. Besides the aorta, we can also carry out in-depth cooperation in medicine, teaching and scientific research on the diagnosis and treatment of diseases such as lower extremity artery and carotid artery," he said.
Professor Feng Rui, deputy director of vascular surgery at Shanghai Changhai Hospital, said.
Zhongshan Hospital affiliated to Xiamen University and Shanghai Changhai Hospital signed a contract to set up "Li Zhaoshen Famous Medicine Studio" in the department of gastroenterology in 2018.
Professor Huang Xiaojin, Director of Vascular Surgery of the hospital, said in an interview with CNN.com that the hospital also has a long history of communication with Changhai Hospital. This time, the two hospitals officially formed a cooperative unit, bringing the cooperation and exchange between the two sides to a new level.
He said that the hospital will regularly invite Shanghai experts to come to the building to carry out surgical technology exchange, teaching room inspection and discussion of difficult cases. At the same time, it will further carry out remote consultation. At present, it plans to conduct remote consultation once a week. In addition, the department will also select personnel for further study and exchange, and strengthen the training and development of the talent team in disciplines.
The reporter learned at the meeting that vascular disease is the leading cause of death in China, and the aorta plays an important role as the main route for all organs of the human body, flowing from the heart to the whole body.
The occurrence of aortic diseases is often accompanied by high risk, high mortality and high difficulty in treatment. The thickest section of the aorta is up to 4 cm in diameter. Once a hemangioma is formed, a rupture occurs, or a rupture of the lining of the blood vessel produces a dissection, which can lead to heavy bleeding. It is very dangerous.
In recent years, as people's lifestyles have changed and the pace of life has accelerated, China has become the largest country in the world for hypertension, and the number of aortic diseases has also increased. Now, with the development of surgical techniques and industrial materials, the treatment of aortic diseases has continued to develop in a minimally invasive, rapid and efficient direction.
Doctors can properly "channel" blood flow by puncturing the thigh and placing a stent in the aorta, thus avoiding the impact on the aneurysm or ruptured dissection and achieving good results. Some surgeries even require only local anesthesia.
More than a dozen domestic experts were invited to the symposium to discuss the new progress in the treatment of aortic diseases, and to carry out cutting-edge technical training and discussion of difficult cases in the form of conference salons.
Reporters learned at the meeting that with the development of surgical techniques and industrial materials, the current treatment of aortic diseases continues to develop in the direction of minimally invasive, rapid and efficient.
