The Longest High-Speed Rail Tunnel in the Three Gorges Reservoir Area - Zhongxin
2020-07-26 17:34:48 Source: China News Network Author: Chen Haifeng Responsible Editor: Chen Haifeng
The picture shows the construction site of the Little Three Gorges Tunnel.
Map of China Railway Chengdu Bureau Group Corporation
Chongqing, July 26 (Reporter Han Lu) reporter learned from China Railway Chengdu Bureau Group Co., Ltd on the 26th that the 18.9-kilometer-long Zhengwan High-Speed Railway Xiaosanxia Tunnel was completed on the same day.
It is understood that the Little Three Gorges Tunnel is not only the longest high-speed rail tunnel within the Three Gorges Reservoir Area, but also the longest single-hole, double-track high-speed rail tunnel with a design speed of 350 kilometers per hour, which is currently under construction in China.
Zhengwan high-speed railway is located in Henan, Hubei and Chongqing provinces and cities. It connects Beijing-Guangzhou and Xulan high-speed railway in Zhengzhou north and Yuwan high-speed railway in Wanzhou south to Chongqing. It is an important part of the "eight longitudinal and eight horizontal" high-speed railway network in China along the river and the Huonantong Road.
The Little Three Gorges Tunnel of Zhengwan-Wan High-Speed Railway was completed on the 26th.
The picture shows through the scene.
The Zhengwan high-speed railway starts in Zhengzhou City, Henan Province, and runs southwest through Pingdingshan City, Nanyang City, and Xiangyang City, Hubei Province, to Wanzhou District, Chongqing. The new line is about 818 kilometers long, with a design speed of 350 kilometers per hour, and about 184 kilometers in Chongqing.
Among them, the Zhengzhou-Xiangyang section was opened for operation on December 1,2019, and the Chongqing section is stepping up construction.
The Little Three Gorges Tunnel, which was completed on the 26th, is a control project for the Zhengwan-Wan high-speed railway. The project is located at the junction of Fengjie County and Wushan County in Chongqing, with a total length of 18.9 kilometers and a maximum burial depth of 890 meters.
Construction of the tunnel began in February 2017, and the entire line was opened on July 26,2020.
According to Wang Guojun, head of Zhengwan High-speed Railway Tunnel Design Co., Ltd., China Railway Second Academy Engineering Group Co., Ltd., the surveying and designing party, the location of the Little Three Gorges Tunnel is very complicated in terms of topography and geological conditions, and it faces risks such as karst, mud-gushing water, and large deformation of soft rock. It is a Grade I high-risk tunnel, and the tunnel design and construction is extremely difficult.
"During the construction of the project, we used geological survey method, geophysical prospecting method and advanced drilling method to advance the geological forecast, and adopted a special design scheme for more than 30 karst caves of various types. For example, we designed and built a bridge with a length of 24 meters, and crossed a large karst cave with a longitudinal length of more than 10 meters and a depth of more than 55 meters in the tunnel to avoid the settlement of the tunnel," said Wang Guojun.
According to the China Railway Tunnel Bureau of the construction party, when the tunnel was constructed, the combination of diversion and plugging was adopted to ensure the orderly progress of the project through the construction of Hengdong flat guide, grouting and plugging, strengthening the structural support of the tunnel and the construction of a sewage treatment station. At the same time, it also avoided the damage of construction and drainage to the water body of the Little Three Gorges Scenic Area. At the same time, it successfully overcame the construction problems such as the bad geology such as the large deformation of soft rock up to 7 kilometers long, and the maximum daily water inrush of 157,000 cubic meters of mud and water.
After the completion and opening of the entire Zhengwan high-speed railway line, it will become a new convenient and fast main passageway to the Central Plains, North China and Northeast China in southwest China. It is of great significance to improve the capacity and quality of the Northeast to Northeast railway passageway in southwest China, improve the layout of the regional road network, speed up the development of tourism resources and urbanization along the route, promote the coordinated development of the region, and promote the implementation of the strategy for the development of the western region.
