According to the announcement, in order to further deepen the reform of state-owned enterprises, optimize the structural adjustment of state-owned capital layout, and improve the equity structure of Greenland, Shanghai Real Estate (Group) Co., Ltd. (Hereinafter referred to as "Shanghai Real Estate") and Shanghai City Investment (Group) Co., Ltd. (Hereinafter referred to as "Shanghai City Investment") intend to transfer part of the company's shares by way of public solicitation of transferees, and the total proportion of the shares to be transferred shall not exceed 17.5% of the total share capital of Greenland.
The price of the shares to be transferred shall not be lower than the higher of the following two: The arithmetic average of the daily weighted average price for the 30 trading days prior to the suggestive announcement date (July 27,2020); and the audited net asset value per share of the Company for the most recent fiscal year.
At present, the jury is still out on the new strategic investors in Greenland. According to the information published in the announcement, it is estimated that the new strategic investors will have to pay about 14 billion yuan to take the 17.5% equity transferred in the mixed reform of Greenland.
It is worth noting that after the completion of the share transfer, it is expected that Greenland will still have no controlling shareholder or actual controller, but the control structure may change greatly.
Since its inception, Greenland Holdings has carried out a number of institutional reforms: From 1992 to 1997, it operated in accordance with market-oriented rules under a purely state-owned system; from 1997 to 2013, it established and continuously improved a joint-stock system of state-owned holding and employee holding; from 2013 to 2015, it introduced strategic investors to form a mixed ownership system in which state-owned and non-public capital are cross-owned and integrated with each other; and from 2015 to the present, it has been listed as a public company.
Greenland's current hybrid reform plan is similar to Gree's. In December 2019, Zhuhai Mingjun, led by High-end Capital, took over the 15% stake of Gree Electric (000651.SZ) for 41.662 billion yuan, and Gree Group retired as a minority shareholder. After the completion of the hybrid reform, Gree Electric implemented modern enterprise management methods, such as executive incentive plan and no real controller structure.
Shanghai Real Estate and Shanghai City Investment are state-owned enterprise groups wholly owned by Shanghai State-owned Assets Supervision and Administration Commission (SASAC). Zhang Yuliang, chairman and president of Greenland Holdings, said that Greenland's move is an important measure for Shanghai to promote the comprehensive reform of state-owned enterprises and accelerate the reform of state-owned enterprises in the new stage in accordance with the requirements of the CPC Central Committee. It fully demonstrates the new ideas of reform adapted to local conditions and tailor-made. By introducing new outstanding strategic shareholders to listed companies, Greenland supports enterprises to further improve the degree of marketization, enhance the freedom of operation and management, and accelerate the full release of reform vitality.
