Dapeng director's "Good luck" shortlisted for Golden Goblet Award - Xinhuanet
On July 18, the 23rd Shanghai International Film Festival announced the official selection of films for the Golden Goblet Award.
Director Dapeng's first reality-themed film, "Good luck," was successfully shortlisted for the Golden Goblet Award at this year's festival. Meanwhile, the film's first poster was released officially.
Photo Gallery of Poster
The film "Good luck" is Dapeng's first reality-themed work, and it is also his second marriage with the Golden Goblet.
The film tells the story of a comedy director who, on a whim, returns to his hometown in rural Northeast China, hoping to turn his family's New Year into a literary film. As a result, he suffers a series of accidents.
The family members, who had gathered for the film, finished the final party.
In the movie poster released today, Wang Jixiang, a member of the family known as "Third Uncle," sits in the center of the screen smoking a cigarette. In the background, the black land of Northeast China is draped in silver, and in the foreground, the red lanterns that the Chinese people must hang for the holidays.
The red lantern, a symbol of festivity and reunion, contrasts sharply with Wang Jixiang, a lonely figure, and seems to reveal the intricacies and tangles in the relationship between the extended family.
