Yu Wang, a platoon leader, and a soldier stand guard at the Zhuokang outpost in Ba Nong.
In this place, where the average annual temperature is minus a dozen degrees, a simple row of barracks stands at the mountain pass. Not far from the barracks, a national flag flutters in the wind. The soldiers stand guard in the wind every day, and at the same time, they have to patrol the higher elevation regularly.
The soldiers had to use their hands and feet to climb up the steep slope of the rocks.
It was late July, when flowers and plants flourished at lower elevations, and in Barong Zhuokang, only the ravine behind the barracks was relatively dense with green.
Gao Peng, a soldier who has been stationed at the outpost for six years, pointed to the ravine and said that this is their back garden. Every year, only in July and August, the grass grows slowly. Soon after, it all turns yellow and is covered with snow.
Patrolling on foot can take up to nine hours.
Under the harsh conditions of the plateau, the soldiers stationed here keep company with the snow-capped mountains and glaciers all the year round, and they have to patrol the mountain passes at higher elevations regularly.
A few days ago, a patrol team composed of eight soldiers, led by instructor Liang Yixin, once again embarked on the patrol road.
Each soldier weighed about 30 pounds and marched to the target early in the morning.
On the way, a soldier rebelled, and his comrades rushed to rescue him.
In addition to the patrol duties, the soldiers at the Barong Zhuokang post have to carry out tactical and physical training every day.
As the minutes ticked by, the elevation rose, the oxygen levels got lower and lower, and the physical strength was constantly overstretched, these factors tested the will of the patrol members.
They clenched their teeth and persisted, crossing several landslides one after the other and several emergency and dangerous beaches.
At about 16:00, it was lunchtime for the patrol members. They took out their own dry food and sat on the ground at an altitude of more than 5,700 meters, accompanied by sleet and snow, and used food to replenish their strength.
The soldiers at the Zhuokang sentry post in Ba Nong conducted tactical and physical training.
During the break, they would play cards together, and the losers would do push-ups, both to entertain and to exercise.
After a short break in the cold wind, they climbed to the target location of the patrol, took out the national flag on the mountain pass, and solemnly swore an oath.
Behind them are snow-capped mountains, and in front of them are tens of kilometers of no man's land. They are the safest guardians of the country.
Beijing Consumption Season Restarted - Xinhuanet
Beijing has restarted the activities of the Beijing consumption season in accordance with the principle of "comprehensive restart, key planning, orderly promotion and strict organization."
On July 26,1.5 million government and enterprise vouchers were issued, including 1 million offline food and beverage shopping vouchers and 500,000 smart product vouchers, which can be collected by consumers in the JD.com APP.
Liu Meiying, deputy director of the Beijing Municipal Bureau of Commerce, said at the media briefing held on the 25th that the consumption season after the restart will further reduce the capital allocation of enterprises on the basis of maintaining the existing preferential subsidies for consumer voucher card packages.
Starting from the first half of August, the current 1:1 capital allocation for the government and enterprises will be adjusted to 2:1. For example, if the original consumer receives a card package to spend at the store, he can enjoy a discount of 120 yuan, including a government subsidy of 60 yuan and a profit of 60 yuan for the enterprise. After the adjustment, the government subsidy will be 80 yuan and the profit of the enterprise will be 40 yuan.
During the consumption season, the three major carriers will subsidize traffic and terminals around 5G consumption, further boosting Beijing's new 5G infrastructure and 5G consumption.
