"Chinese Doctors" To Pay Tribute to Anti-Epidemic Heroes - Xinhua
Recently, with the respect of the heroes of Chinese filmmakers fighting the epidemic, Yu Dong, Chairman of Bona Films Group, and Liu Weiqiang (pictured left), Director of Bona Films Group, had a discussion and exchange with academician Zhong Nanshan in Guangzhou on the filming and production of the anti-epidemic film "Chinese Doctors."
With "Chinese Doctor," Bona Films hopes to pay tribute to all the medical and epidemic prevention workers who are fighting on the frontline of epidemic prevention and control.
In 2021, the film will be released nationally as a tribute film to celebrate the 100th anniversary of the founding of the Communist Party of China.
At present, under the arrangement of the Central Propaganda Department and the State Film Bureau, and with the support of the Guangdong Film Bureau and the Hubei Film Bureau, Bona Films has organized the original cast of the film "China's Captain" to prepare the film "China's Doctor," which is a film reflecting the strong leadership of the CPC Central Committee and the unity of the people of the whole country in fighting the epidemic of New Crown Pneumonia.
Focusing on the frontline of the fight against the epidemic in Wuhan, the film will feature the Wuhan medical staff and the provincial and municipal medical aid teams as the characters' backgrounds. From the perspective of human nature, the film will use the unique narrative, as well as the highly impactful camera language, to show the touching stories of the Chinese medical staff on the frontline of the fight against the epidemic with dedication and sacrifice.
It is understood that on the first day of the unsealing of Wuhan, Bona overcame many difficulties, dispatched a team of photographers to the frontline of the epidemic, and had face-to-face exchanges with hundreds of medical workers to understand and collect information. At present, Bona has interviewed academician Zhong Nanshan himself, the first person from Guangzhou to assist Wuhan, the medical team from Guangdong to assist Hubei, as well as the angels in white who are at the forefront of the anti-epidemic front such as Wuhan Jinyintan Hospital, Wuhan Union Hospital, Zhongnan Hospital of Wuhan University and Wuhan Central Hospital, and filmed a large number of precious first-hand video materials.
Academician Zhong Nanshan also raised expectations and hopes for the filming of the film during the symposium: "I am looking forward to it. I hope you will not only visit some experts who have made more appearances, but also interview more medical workers who are working hard on the frontline. They are the majority of them."
He said that he had seen "Me and My Motherland" and "Captain China" before, and thought that it would be a good way to tell the story of the big pattern from the perspective of ordinary people.
"Now some foreign friends still have some misunderstandings about China."
Commenting on the spread of the film, academician Zhong Nanshan said that at present, some people abroad like to label the virus as political. He hoped that the film could impress the audience from the perspective of human nature: "Besides being screened in China, this film is best to be screened abroad, in a way that both domestic and foreign audiences can understand, and to impress the audience with the true humanistic spirit."
Academician Zhong Nanshan also fondly recalled the film "Man to Middle Age" in the 1980s. "After all these years, what impressed me most about the film after the reform and opening up was" Man to Middle Age. "At that time, all my friends who were doctors abroad cried. If" Chinese Doctor "could play such a role, it would be very remarkable."
Academician Zhong Nanshan said that if "Chinese Doctors" could resonate with foreign audiences, it would be very successful.
During the discussion and exchange, academician Zhong Nanshan also shared his opinions and suggestions on the current international epidemic prevention and control. "I believe people will always be smarter than the virus," he said.
Academician Zhong Nanshan said that although the virus is difficult to predict, since the primitive society, mankind has passed through a thousand difficulties and risks. Nowadays, modern society has developed medical science and technology and social management measures. Coupled with the fact that medical workers and even ordinary people all over the world have a basic understanding of the scientific response to the epidemic of New Crown Pneumonia, people will no longer be as passive as before. "Next, we should pay attention to two aspects of work, one is to study how the whole world can strengthen cooperation, and the other is to focus on the consolation of people's hearts."
(Journalist Wang Jinyue)
