Telecom Network Fraud Crimes Rise by 70% in the First Half of the Year Summary of Highest Inspection Characteristics - Zhongxin
According to the website of the Supreme People's Procuratorate, in the first half of this year, the procuratorial organs across the country prosecuted 58,101 people for fraud crimes, a year-on-year increase of 35 percent.
In particular, among the crimes of obstructing epidemic prevention and control, the number of fraud crimes prosecuted by the procuratorial organs accounted for 43.4% of the total number of crimes of obstructing epidemic prevention and control.
The Supreme People's Procuratorate has given targeted guidance. Of the ten batches of typical cases related to epidemic prevention and control that have been issued so far, nine involved fraud.
From the perspective of the procuratorial organs handling cases in the first half of the year, there were many kinds of crimes involving fraud, ranging from the national macro-policy to the common people's food, clothing and shelter, including epidemic fraud, "medical care" fraud, "health care products" fraud, "enrollment intermediary" fraud, "routine loan" fraud, state subsidy fraud, national assets unfreezing fraud, etc., constantly "innovating," covering education, medical care, employment, old-age pension, social security, land requisition and relocation, precise poverty alleviation, financial credit and other fields, which not only caused economic losses to the victims, but also seriously affected economic and social development.
In particular, some telecom network frauds break through the limits of national borders, regions and personnel, and have the characteristics of stakeholder, cross-border, remote and electronic payment. There are not many specific groups of victims, which can cause great harm.
For example, some set up special companies, rent high-grade office buildings, set up multiple departments or posts, use legitimate online platforms to publicize and recruit, train and evaluate recruiters, adopt enterprise operation mode management, cloak themselves in "legal cloak," and become more confusing.
It is incumbent upon the procuratorial organs to punish and prevent crimes according to law and issue early warning to the public and relevant departments in a timely manner.
In handling cases judicially, the procuratorial organs earnestly perform their duties, not only maintaining a high-pressure posture against fraud crimes, but also refining various law enforcement measures in a targeted manner, and promoting social governance through the production and issuance of procuratorial recommendations.
The procuratorial organs strictly control the facts, evidence, procedure and application of the law in cases of arrest and prosecution of fraud, and take the facts as the basis and the law as the yardstick, so as not to be wronged or not to indulge.
Especially for the telecom network fraud crime, we should pay attention to the central role of electronic data in fact-finding, and strive to build a chain of evidence between electronic data, verbal evidence and documentary evidence.
For example, the Yinzhou District Procuratorate of Ningbo City, Zhejiang Province handled a certain epidemic fraud case, and the procuratorial organ intervened in advance at the first time. From the case to the conclusion, it took only 5 days, reflecting the attitude and determination to handle the case quickly and strictly and maintain the overall stability of the society.
During the examination of arrest and prosecution, attention is paid to the prosecution of missing offenders in cases, correcting the omission of 733 arrests by public security organs, and correcting the omission of the public security organs to examine and prosecute 1,113 accomplices.
In the first half of the year, the national procuratorial organs issued 298 prosecutorial recommendations in response to fraud crimes, promoting joint efforts to prevent fraud crimes and promoting deep-seated governance.
For example, the Guangzhou Procuratorate of Guangdong Province and the Dongguan Procuratorate of Guangdong Province put forward timely recommendations on the loopholes in the supervision of telecommunications networks, such as communication enterprises, banks and intermediary organizations found in handling cases, urging the relevant units to strengthen supervision and improve the mechanism, so as to promote the construction of long-term system.
