Membrane Separation Technology Helps Hack the "Greenhouse Effect"
Schematic diagram of a new hybrid matrix membrane preparation technology
Our reporter Shang Rui reported: Recently, the atmospheric environment and bioenergy team of Tianjin University has made significant progress in the "membrane separation method to capture carbon dioxide," and successfully developed a new hybrid matrix membrane preparation technology, which greatly improves the carbon dioxide capture performance of membrane materials.
The results have been published as the cover article of the international journal "Greenhouse Gas: Science and Technology."
The "greenhouse effect" is a major environmental problem that perplexes human development, while carbon dioxide emissions are the culprit of the "greenhouse effect."
How to efficiently capture and utilize the carbon dioxide emitted by human beings is the focus of scientists' attention.
"Membrane Separation" is a new technology of carbon dioxide capture. It separates carbon dioxide gas with the help of membrane material, which has the characteristics of high efficiency and energy saving, and simple operation.
