The research team of Tianjin University innovated ideas to explore the influence of different solvents on the separation performance of membrane gases through repeated experiments.
The experimental results show that N-methylpyrrolidone is used as the preparation solvent, and the carbon nanotubes in the resulting membrane materials are more evenly distributed and "more breathable," which effectively improves the gas separation efficiency and rate of membrane materials.
The carbon dioxide separation performance of mixed matrix membranes prepared by this new technology is close to the upper limit of the theoretical separation of such membranes.
"The new technology provides a new idea for capturing carbon dioxide by membrane separation."
