Before volunteering to fill in the application form, understand what is the professional grade difference - CNN.com
2020-07-27 02:22:36 Source: Chongqing Morning Post Author: Yu Xiao Responsible Editor: Yu Xiao
Before volunteering, understand what is a professional grade difference.
Every year, students or parents who volunteer for the college entrance examination do not understand the nouns involved in the voluntary application, thus affecting the voluntary application.
This year, five universities - Beijing Jiaotong University, Beijing University of Science and Technology, Beijing University of Posts and Telecommunications, Beijing Forestry University and Beijing University of Chemical Technology - jointly issued the 2020 enrollment policy, eliminating the professional grade difference.
What is the meaning of professional grade difference and what is the significance in volunteering?
There are three ways to allocate professional rules
Experts reminded that before volunteering, you must read the "Admissions Charter" of your preferred school in detail to understand the admission rules of colleges and universities, including the adjustment ratio, professional allocation rules, etc.
The rules of professional assignment refer to the three main ways of professional priority, score priority and professional grade difference for the admission of majors after the adjustment of university files.
The specific method used by colleges and universities will be clearly defined in the "Admissions Charter."
But there are some colleges and universities whose admission principle is to give priority to the total score, and there is no grade difference between the majors.
That is to say, candidates within the scope of admission will be lined up according to the total score. When the score does not reach the first major voluntary admission score line, it will be determined whether the second major voluntary admission score line has been reached, and so on until the admission to the last major voluntary, there will be no grade difference between the professional volunteers.
The so-called "professional grade difference" is when an institution arranges a candidate's major, according to one or several scores published in the enrollment regulations, to determine the admission of candidates from different majors. This kind of grade difference is the "professional grade difference."
That is, the difference between the scores of the first major and the non-first major when the college admits the candidates, and the difference between the grades of each major, such as 3,2,1, etc.
Take, for example.
Assuming that Xiao Ming, a student, enrolled in A University and scored 560 points, his major volunteers were: Computer, international trade, automation, mechanical engineering, electronic commerce, and the method of professional grade difference was implemented for admission to A University. The grade difference was divided into 2,1,1, and 0 points.
At the time of professional assignment, if Xiaoming's first major voluntarily meets the requirements for professional admission and the major has a planned balance, then Xiaoming will be admitted to the "computer" major; if the computer is not admitted, his score will be subtracted by 2 points, according to the ranking of 558 points with the candidates who voluntarily apply for "international trade" in the first major, to determine whether they meet the requirements for professional admission; if they are still unable to meet the requirements, the score will be subtracted by 1 point (i.e. 557 points) for voluntary "automated" admission in the third major; if they are still unable to meet the requirements, the score will be subtracted by 1 point (i.e. 556 points) for admission to the fourth major, and if the subsequent major is still unable to meet its professional requirements, the score will no longer be subtracted, and so on.
Different universities have different levels of specialization.
With the popularization of parallel volunteering, many colleges and universities have now abolished the professional grade difference. However, some colleges and universities still retain this method this year. Judging from the "Admissions Charter" published by each university, more than 20 universities have set up professional grade difference this year.
For example, Sichuan Agricultural University, Shandong University of Science and Technology, Heilongjiang University of Traditional Chinese Medicine, Jiangsu University of Science and Technology, Jiangxi Normal University, Chengdu Medical College, Northeast Electric Power University, Jimei University, Nanjing Medical University, Nanjing University of Technology, Ningxia University, Shandong University of Science and Technology, China Civil Aviation Flight Academy, etc.
In each of these universities, there is a difference in the professional grade.
Some colleges and universities have a grade difference in each major, such as Ningxia University, where the files have been submitted to the candidates, who are admitted according to the order in which the candidates fill in the professional volunteers, one point in turn, and then one point in order of the scores.
However, some universities have set up different professional grade differences between different majors.
For example, Jimei University has a total score of 4 points for professional volunteers, that is, 3 points for volunteers in the first major and 3 points for volunteers in other majors. There is no grade difference between volunteers in other majors, which is regarded as parallel volunteers. The difference between volunteers in other majors and volunteers in adjustment majors is 1 point.
When volunteering, candidates and their parents must carefully read the admission policies of the schools to see if there is any difference in professional grade and what is the form of the difference in grade. While fully considering the scores, they should also make a reasonable analysis of the schools and majors to be selected. If the institutions clearly adopt the method of difference in grade in the admission regulations, candidates should pay attention to the gradient between the majors and improve the chances of admission when choosing a major.
